<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<p class="p">Let 
 <div id="IEq1" class="inline-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <alternatives class="alternatives" xmlns="">
   <tex-math id="M1" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$X_{id}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <div id="M2" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <div class="msub">
     <span class="mi">X</span>
     <div class="mrow">
      <span class="mi">i</span>
      <span class="mi">d</span>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
   <span xlink:href="40064_2015_1536_Article_IEq1.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </div> denote the 
 <div id="IEq2" class="inline-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <alternatives class="alternatives" xmlns="">
   <tex-math id="M3" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$i{\text{th}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <div id="M4" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <div class="mrow">
     <span class="mi">i</span>
     <span class="mtext">th</span>
    </div>
   </div>
   <span xlink:href="40064_2015_1536_Article_IEq2.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </div> vulnerability indicator in the 
 <div id="IEq3" class="inline-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <alternatives class="alternatives" xmlns="">
   <tex-math id="M5" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$d{\text{th}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <div id="M6" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <div class="mrow">
     <span class="mi">d</span>
     <span class="mtext">th</span>
    </div>
   </div>
   <span xlink:href="40064_2015_1536_Article_IEq3.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </div> canton 
 <div id="IEq4" class="inline-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <alternatives class="alternatives" xmlns="">
   <tex-math id="M7" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$({\text{i.e.}}\, i = 1,2, \ldots ,m;\;d = 1,2, \ldots n)$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <div id="M8" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <div class="mrow">
     <span stretchy="false" class="mo">(</span>
     <span class="mtext">i.e.</span>
     <span width="0.166667em" class="mspace"/>
     <span class="mi">i</span>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <span class="mn">1</span>
     <span class="mo">,</span>
     <span class="mn">2</span>
     <span class="mo">,</span>
     <span class="mo">…</span>
     <span class="mo">,</span>
     <span class="mi">m</span>
     <span class="mo">;</span>
     <span width="0.277778em" class="mspace"/>
     <span class="mi">d</span>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <span class="mn">1</span>
     <span class="mo">,</span>
     <span class="mn">2</span>
     <span class="mo">,</span>
     <span class="mo">…</span>
     <span class="mi">n</span>
     <span stretchy="false" class="mo">)</span>
    </div>
   </div>
   <span xlink:href="40064_2015_1536_Article_IEq4.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </div>. We normalize each indicator such that 
 <div id="IEq5" class="inline-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <alternatives class="alternatives" xmlns="">
   <tex-math id="M9" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$y_{id} = \frac{{X_{id} - Min_{d} X_{id} }}{{Max_{d} X_{id} - Min_{d} X_{id} }}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <div id="M10" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <div class="mrow">
     <div class="msub">
      <span class="mi">y</span>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">i</span>
       <span class="mi">d</span>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <div class="mfrac">
      <div class="mrow">
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">X</span>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">i</span>
         <span class="mi">d</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">-</span>
       <span class="mi">M</span>
       <span class="mi">i</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">n</span>
        <span class="mi">d</span>
       </div>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">X</span>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">i</span>
         <span class="mi">d</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">M</span>
       <span class="mi">a</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">x</span>
        <span class="mi">d</span>
       </div>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">X</span>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">i</span>
         <span class="mi">d</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">-</span>
       <span class="mi">M</span>
       <span class="mi">i</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">n</span>
        <span class="mi">d</span>
       </div>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">X</span>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">i</span>
         <span class="mi">d</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
   <span xlink:href="40064_2015_1536_Article_IEq5.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </div> if the indicator is assumed to be positively associated to vulnerability, or 
 <div id="IEq6" class="inline-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <alternatives class="alternatives" xmlns="">
   <tex-math id="M11" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$y_{id} = \frac{{Max_{d} X_{id} - X_{id} }}{{Max_{d} X_{id} - Min_{d} X_{id} }}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <div id="M12" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <div class="mrow">
     <div class="msub">
      <span class="mi">y</span>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">i</span>
       <span class="mi">d</span>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <div class="mfrac">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">M</span>
       <span class="mi">a</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">x</span>
        <span class="mi">d</span>
       </div>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">X</span>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">i</span>
         <span class="mi">d</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">-</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">X</span>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">i</span>
         <span class="mi">d</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">M</span>
       <span class="mi">a</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">x</span>
        <span class="mi">d</span>
       </div>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">X</span>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">i</span>
         <span class="mi">d</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">-</span>
       <span class="mi">M</span>
       <span class="mi">i</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">n</span>
        <span class="mi">d</span>
       </div>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">X</span>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">i</span>
         <span class="mi">d</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
   <span xlink:href="40064_2015_1536_Article_IEq6.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </div> otherwise. From the matrix of normalized values, 
 <div id="IEq7" class="inline-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <alternatives class="alternatives" xmlns="">
   <tex-math id="M13" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$Y_{{\left[ {n\;\times\;m} \right]}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <div id="M14" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <div class="msub">
     <span class="mi">Y</span>
     <div close="]" open="[" separators="" class="mfenced">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">n</span>
       <span width="0.277778em" class="mspace"/>
       <span class="mo">×</span>
       <span width="0.277778em" class="mspace"/>
       <span class="mi">m</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
   <span xlink:href="40064_2015_1536_Article_IEq7.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </div>, the composite vulnerability indicator for the 
 <div id="IEq8" class="inline-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <alternatives class="alternatives" xmlns="">
   <tex-math id="M15" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$d{\text{th}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <div id="M16" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <div class="mrow">
     <span class="mi">d</span>
     <span class="mtext">th</span>
    </div>
   </div>
   <span xlink:href="40064_2015_1536_Article_IEq8.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </div> canton is constructed as follows:
 <disp-formula id="Equ1" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">1</label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M17" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$y_{d} = w_{1} y_{d1} + w_{2} y_{d2} + \cdots + w_{m} y_{dm}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <div id="M18" display="block" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <div class="mrow">
     <div class="msub">
      <span class="mi">y</span>
      <span class="mi">d</span>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <div class="msub">
      <span class="mi">w</span>
      <span class="mn">1</span>
     </div>
     <div class="msub">
      <span class="mi">y</span>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">d</span>
       <span class="mn">1</span>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">+</span>
     <div class="msub">
      <span class="mi">w</span>
      <span class="mn">2</span>
     </div>
     <div class="msub">
      <span class="mi">y</span>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">d</span>
       <span class="mn">2</span>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">+</span>
     <span class="mo">⋯</span>
     <span class="mo">+</span>
     <div class="msub">
      <span class="mi">w</span>
      <span class="mi">m</span>
     </div>
     <div class="msub">
      <span class="mi">y</span>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">d</span>
       <span class="mi">m</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
   <graphic xlink:href="40064_2015_1536_Article_Equ1.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>
 <div id="IEq9" class="inline-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <alternatives class="alternatives" xmlns="">
   <tex-math id="M19" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$w_{i}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <div id="M20" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <div class="msub">
     <span class="mi">w</span>
     <span class="mi">i</span>
    </div>
   </div>
   <span xlink:href="40064_2015_1536_Article_IEq9.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </div> is the weight of each indicator, that is, its contribution to the formation of the composite vulnerability indicator, where 
 <div id="IEq10" class="inline-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <alternatives class="alternatives" xmlns="">
   <tex-math id="M21" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$0 &lt; w_{i} &lt; 1$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <div id="M22" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <div class="mrow">
     <span class="mn">0</span>
     <span class="mo">&lt;</span>
     <div class="msub">
      <span class="mi">w</span>
      <span class="mi">i</span>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">&lt;</span>
     <span class="mn">1</span>
    </div>
   </div>
   <span xlink:href="40064_2015_1536_Article_IEq10.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </div> and 
 <div id="IEq11" class="inline-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <alternatives class="alternatives" xmlns="">
   <tex-math id="M23" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$w_{1} + w_{2} + \cdots + w_{m} = 1$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <div id="M24" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <div class="mrow">
     <div class="msub">
      <span class="mi">w</span>
      <span class="mn">1</span>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">+</span>
     <div class="msub">
      <span class="mi">w</span>
      <span class="mn">2</span>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">+</span>
     <span class="mo">⋯</span>
     <span class="mo">+</span>
     <div class="msub">
      <span class="mi">w</span>
      <span class="mi">m</span>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <span class="mn">1</span>
    </div>
   </div>
   <span xlink:href="40064_2015_1536_Article_IEq11.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </div>. To estimate the weights, we calculate the variance of each normalized indicator across cantons as 
 <div id="IEq12" class="inline-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <alternatives class="alternatives" xmlns="">
   <tex-math id="M25" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\sigma_{i}^{2} = \frac{{\mathop \sum \nolimits_{d = 1}^{n} \left( {y_{di} - \bar{y}_{i} } \right)^{2} }}{n - 1}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <div id="M26" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <div class="mrow">
     <div class="msubsup">
      <span mathvariant="italic" class="mi">σ</span>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">i</span>
      </div>
      <span class="mn">2</span>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <div class="mfrac">
      <div class="mrow">
       <div class="msubsup">
        <span class="mo">∑</span>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">d</span>
         <span class="mo">=</span>
         <span class="mn">1</span>
        </div>
        <span class="mi">n</span>
       </div>
       <div class="msup">
        <div close=")" open="(" separators="" class="mfenced">
         <div class="mrow">
          <div class="msub">
           <span class="mi">y</span>
           <div class="mrow">
            <span class="mi">d</span>
            <span class="mi">i</span>
           </div>
          </div>
          <span class="mo">-</span>
          <div class="msub">
           <div accent="true" class="mover">
            <div class="mrow">
             <span class="mi">y</span>
            </div>
            <div class="mrow">
             <span stretchy="false" class="mo">¯</span>
            </div>
           </div>
           <span class="mi">i</span>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
        <span class="mn">2</span>
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">n</span>
       <span class="mo">-</span>
       <span class="mn">1</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
   <span xlink:href="40064_2015_1536_Article_IEq12.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </div> where 
 <div id="IEq13" class="inline-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <alternatives class="alternatives" xmlns="">
   <tex-math id="M27" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\bar{y}_{i}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <div id="M28" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <div class="msub">
     <div accent="true" class="mover">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">y</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span stretchy="false" class="mo">¯</span>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mi">i</span>
    </div>
   </div>
   <span xlink:href="40064_2015_1536_Article_IEq13.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </div> is the average value. We define the weights relative to the aggregate behavior of the indicators variability across cantons, that is, weights vary inversely with the variance across the cantons as follows:
 <disp-formula id="Equ2" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">2</label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M29" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$w_{i} = \frac{{\sqrt {\sigma_{i}^{2} } }}{{\mathop \sum \nolimits_{i = 1}^{m} \sqrt {\sigma_{i}^{2} } }}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <div id="M30" display="block" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <div class="mrow">
     <div class="msub">
      <span class="mi">w</span>
      <span class="mi">i</span>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <div class="mfrac">
      <div class="msqrt">
       <div class="msubsup">
        <span mathvariant="italic" class="mi">σ</span>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">i</span>
        </div>
        <span class="mn">2</span>
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <div class="msubsup">
        <span class="mo">∑</span>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">i</span>
         <span class="mo">=</span>
         <span class="mn">1</span>
        </div>
        <span class="mi">m</span>
       </div>
       <div class="msqrt">
        <div class="msubsup">
         <span mathvariant="italic" class="mi">σ</span>
         <div class="mrow">
          <span class="mi">i</span>
         </div>
         <span class="mn">2</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
   <graphic xlink:href="40064_2015_1536_Article_Equ2.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>This weighting mechanism ensures that large variation in any of the indicators will not dominate the contribution of the rest, and rules out the possibility that, for policy purposes, improvements in an indicator can perfectly compensate detriments in any other.
</p>
